title: Mo Farah and his wife Tania Nell welcome a son: "Buzzing to welcome the new man of the house" - Showbiz
text: Mo Farah and his wife Tania Nell are proud parents of a baby boy.The long-distance runner shared the happy news on Twitter today (October 14).Y !!! It's a boy!!! Buzzing to welcome the new man of the house!!!! Mum and baby doing well!!! #Excitedâ€” Mo Farah (@Mo_Farah) October 14, 2015"Y !!! It's a boy!!! Buzzing to welcome the new man of the house!!!! Mum and baby doing well!!! #Excited," he tweeted.The couple's newborn son joins older twin sisters Aisha and Amani, as well as Tania's daughter Rihanna from a prior marriage.Farah announced that Tania was expecting a baby in August, saying at the time: "So excited to have baby number 4 on the way!!! Y !!!!"The Olympian and Nell have been married since 2010, when they tied the knot in London in a ceremony attended by the likes of Hayley Yelling and Jo Pavey.
